Hash: SHA1

SUPPORT COMMUNICATION - SECURITY BULLETIN

Document ID: c00629555
Version: 3

HPSBUX02108 SSRT061133 rev.3 - HP-UX running Sendmail, Remote
Execution of Arbitrary Code

NOTICE: The information in this Security Bulletin should be acted
upon as soon as possible.

Release Date: 2006-04-04
Last Updated: 2006-04-05

Potential Security Impact: Remote Execution of Arbitrary Code

Source: Hewlett-Packard Company,
        HP Software Security Response Team

VULNERABILITY SUMMARY
A vulnerability has been identified in Sendmail which may allow a
remote attacker to execute arbitrary code.

References: CVE-2006-0058

SUPPORTED SOFTWARE VERSIONS*: ONLY impacted versions are listed.
HP-UX B.11.11, B.11.23.

BACKGROUND

CERT has published a vulnerability report available at:
http://www.kb.cert.org/vuls/id/834865

This bulletin will be revised as other versions of Sendmail become
available.

To determine if an HP-UX system has an affected version,
search the output of "swlist -a revision -l fileset"
for one of the filesets listed below. For affected systems
verify that the recommended action has been taken.

AFFECTED VERSIONS

For sendmail 8.13.3
HP-UX B.11.11
==========
SMAIL-UPGRADE.INETSVCS-SMAIL, revision=B.11.11.02.001
action: install update to Rev. 2.002 or subsequent

HP-UX B.11.23
==========
SMAIL-UPGRADE.INET-SMAIL, revision=B.11.23.1.001
action: install update to Rev. 2.002 or subsequent

 ->InternetSrvcs.INETSVCS2-RUN,fr=B.11.23,fa=HP-UX_B.11.23_IA,v=HP
 ->InternetSrvcs.INETSVCS2-RUN,fr=B.11.23,fa=HP-UX_B.11.23_PA,v=HP
 ->action: install UNOF_INET31734_1.depot or subsequent

END AFFECTED VERSIONS

RESOLUTION

HP has made the following software updates available to resolve
the issue. The software updates can be downloaded via ftp from:

System: hprc.external.hp.com (192.170.19.100)
Login: sendmail
Password: sendmail (NOTE: CASE-sensitive)

ftp://sendmail:sendmail@...c.external.hp.com /
or
ftp://sendmail:sendmail@....170.19.100/

The README.txt contains cksum and md5 output for the preliminary
depots.

cksum ./sendmail-8.13_1123.depot
 ->692720776 15759360 sendmail-8.13_1123.depot
md5 ./sendmail-8.13_1123.depot
 ->E09933A4AECC16B97A8F7ACF07060F84
cksum sendmail-8.13_1111.depot
954959898 5130240 sendmail-8.13_1111.depot
md5 ./sendmail-8.13_1111.depot
C85EFD8AEDB16EEF1DF0FF65988350C0

 ->#cksum *
 ->3327957574 3317760 UNOF_INET31734_1.depot
 ->2096860596 7487 UNOF_INET31734_1.text
 ->#md5 UNOF_INET31734_1.depot B17A7F5566214B35E983B3F53C309A17
 ->#md5 UNOF_INET31734_1.text 565F7963B77BEE3EB2825990F60D1F6D

After installation, the output of "sendmail -bs" will include the
following information.
sendmail -bs versioning:
@(#)Sendmail version 8.13.3 - Revision 2.002 - 2006/03/25


MANUAL ACTIONS: Yes - Update
HP-UX B.11.11 - install preliminary software updates
from ftp server
HP-UX B.11.23 - install preliminary software updates
from ftp server


